          <h3>Stand-up</h3>

          <p>Oliver first appeared at the Edinburgh Festival Fringe in 2001 as part of The Comedy Zone, a late-night
            showcase of
            newer acts, where he played the character of an "oleaginous journalist". At the Festival and similar venues,
            Oliver
            frequently worked with other members of the Chocolate Milk Gang, a group of comedians who often collaborated
            and
            performed with one another, including Daniel Kitson, Russell Howard, David Oâ€™Doherty, and Alun Cochrane. He
